        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:12PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 911 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Leslie to 7 miles southwest of Stockbridge
to near Cement City to near Morenci. Movement was northeast at 70
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plainfield, Hudson Mills Metropark, Ridgeway, Sand Creek, Conway
Township, Medina, Chelsea, Chilson, Dexter, Deerfield, Unadilla,
Holloway, Deerfield Township, Dixboro, Morenci, Seneca, Pittsfield
Township, Macon, Munson, and Ypsilanti.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
